commit.message:
Using python's os.pathsep to seperate env vars (#14)

The os.pathsep turns into ":" on unix and ";" on windows, allowing
windows paths to contain the colon as part of their drive.

For example, using:

set PYSNMPMIBDIRS=C:\local\mibs;C:\src\mibs

Will now work on windows, on unix one can keep doing

PYSNMPMIBDIRS=/home/myuser/mibs:/srv/local/mibs

Add LICENSE.rst to MANIFEST.in (#11)

Signed-off-by: Asaf Kahlon <asafka7@gmail.com>
Add numeric IPv6 format note in the docs
Add usage note on IPv6 address

Add five-zero security engine ID for localized keys

If the user specifies localized keys, but does not specify security
engine ID (-e), the magic value of 0x0000000000 will be automatically
associated with given localized keys to use them with any unknown
authoritative SNMP engine.

Add support for master or localized SNMPv3 USM keys

This change bumps pysnmp requirement to GitHub HEAD

PEP8 the whole project (#8)

In particular:

* imports reordered
* constants uppercased
* dubdles removed
* spaces between lines added
* exit(-1) -> exit(1)
